&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 20&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47865923</guid><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 16:34:21 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Ask HN: In your job with all the AI go-go/execution velocity – are you lonely?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47865907</link><description>&lt;p&gt;I am noticing so many corporate job postings and rhetoric around "AI acceleration" and removing humans.&lt;p&gt;I'm wondering in companies or start-ups where it's all like "yeah let's win" do you have normal/fun/goofing off social time with your co-workers - are you happy or does it feel lonelier?&lt;p&gt;My first growth stage co was a lot of fun mostly because of the random acts of tech company non-sense my team and I joked around with (think Silicon Valley TV show all ways blue or stupid tangent kind of nerdy stuff), but I am noticing in my last 2-3 years everything seems about total execution and these moments seem lost.&lt;p&gt;I get that we want competent team members and want to do well, but I'm genuinely wondering if the workplace is changing to lose a lot of the specialness/aliveness of the "valley feeling" of a tech co.&lt;p&gt;Anecdotal or ?&lt;/p&gt;
